#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Quarkus 4 Update"
msgstr "Quarkus 4 更新"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Before diving into DDD, the hosts shared a brief status update: the main branch has now switched to version 4, meaning new feature development is targeting the 4.x line. On the 3.x side, 3.40 is expected to be the last minor release. The biggest in-flight changes heading into Quarkus 4 include a https://vertx.io/[Vert.x] 5 upgrade and a https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson[Jackson] 3 upgrade — significant library bumps that warrant the major version bump."
msgstr "在深入探讨 DDD 之前，主持人简要介绍了最新进展：主分支现已切换至 4 版，这意味着新功能的开发将以 4.x 系列为目标。在 3.x 方面，预计 3.40 将是最后一个次要版本。 Quarkus 4 即将推出的最大变更包括 link:https://vertx.io/[Vert.x] 5 升级和 link:https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson[Jackson] 3 升级——这些重要的库版本更新足以支撑主版本号的提升。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Demo Application: A Call for Papers"
msgstr "演示应用程序：征稿启事"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy built a https://sessionize.com/[Sessionize]-inspired call-for-papers application to ground the discussion. The application lets speakers browse conferences, submit session proposals, and receive acceptance or rejection notifications. Reviewers can then accept, waitlist, or decline proposals through a review screen."
msgstr "杰里米开发了一个 link:https://sessionize.com/[受 Sessionize 启发的] 征稿应用程序，以促进讨论。该应用程序允许演讲者浏览会议信息、提交议程提案，并接收录用或拒稿通知。评审员随后可通过评审界面对提案进行录用、列入候补名单或拒绝。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The frontend is built with https://docs.quarkiverse.io/quarkus-quinoa/dev/index.html[Quinoa] and https://react.dev/[React]. The full repo can be cloned and run locally with `mvn quarkus:dev` (or the Maven wrapper)."
msgstr "前端采用 link:https://docs.quarkiverse.io/quarkus-quinoa/dev/index.html[Quinoa] 和 link:https://react.dev/[React] 构建。可以克隆整个代码库，并使用 ` `mvn quarkus:dev` `（或 Maven 封装器）在本地运行。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Package Structure and Subdomains"
msgstr "包结构与子域"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The application is organised around two subdomains inside a monolith:"
msgstr "该应用程序围绕单体架构内的两个子域进行组织："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**CFP (Call for Papers)** — handles proposal submission and review"
msgstr "*征稿启事（CFP）* ——负责 *论文* 提案的提交和评审"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Communications** — handles outbound notifications to presenters"
msgstr "*通信* — 负责向演讲者发送外发通知"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy is deliberately pragmatic about package structure: don't be dogmatic, but do make subdomains visible at the top level."
msgstr "杰里米在包结构方面采取了务实的态度：不要墨守成规，但要确保子域在顶级目录中可见。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Walking the Full Request Path"
msgstr "遍历完整的请求路径"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy walked through a proposal submission end-to-end, from the REST adapter to the aggregate and back."
msgstr "杰里米详细演示了提案提交流程的全过程，从 REST 适配器到聚合器，再返回。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Incoming Adapter: REST Resource"
msgstr "入站适配器：REST 资源"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The `SessionProposalResource` is a standard JAX-RS endpoint. It receives a `SessionProposalParameters` object — a plain record that models the JSON coming over the wire — and applies https://jakarta.ee/specifications/bean-validation/[Jakarta Validation] annotations at this layer. This is intentional: frameworks like Jakarta Validation belong at the outer adapter layer, not inside the domain."
msgstr "`SessionProposalResource` 是一个标准的 JAX-RS 端点。它接收一个 `SessionProposalParameters` 对象——这是一个用于建模网络传输中 JSON 数据的普通记录——并在该层应用 link:https://jakarta.ee/specifications/bean-validation/[Jakarta Validation] 注解。这是有意为之：像 Jakarta Validation 这样的框架应位于外部适配器层，而非领域内部。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Commands"
msgstr "命令"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "After validation, the parameters are mapped into a `CreateSessionProposalCommand` — an immutable Java record. The command belongs inside the `application` package because it forms the API through which any adapter (REST, messaging, file transfer) communicates with the application core. Using basic Java validation inside the command, rather than a framework annotation, keeps the internal model framework-agnostic."
msgstr "验证完成后，这些参数会被映射到一个 `CreateSessionProposalCommand` 对象中——这是一个不可变的 Java 记录。 该命令应位于 `应用程序` 包中，因为它构成了任何适配器（REST、消息传递、文件传输）与应用程序核心进行通信的 API。在命令内部使用基本的 Java 验证，而非框架注解，可确保内部模型与框架无关。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The command is then passed to the `CFPApplicationService`."
msgstr "随后，该命令会被传递给 `CFPApplicationService` 。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Application Service"
msgstr "应用服务"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The application service orchestrates the work. Its `createSessionProposal` method can be called from any kind of adapter — that is the core promise of hexagonal architecture. The service:"
msgstr "应用服务负责协调各项工作。其 `createSessionProposal` 方法可由任何类型的适配器调用——这就是六边形架构的核心承诺。该服务："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Builds a `SubmissionContext` (open/close dates, session formats, tracks, existing sessions) so the aggregate can make informed decisions without touching infrastructure"
msgstr "构建一个 `SubmissionContext` （投稿起止日期、会议形式、分会场、现有会议环节），以便汇总系统无需接触基础设施即可做出明智的决策"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Calls the static factory method `SessionProposal.create(command, context)` on the aggregate"
msgstr "调用聚合上的静态工厂方法 `SessionProposal.create(command, context)`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Passes the resulting aggregate to the repository for persistence"
msgstr "将生成的聚合结果传递给存储库以进行持久化"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Returns a DTO"
msgstr "返回一个 DTO"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Aggregate"
msgstr "《聚合》"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`SessionProposal` is the aggregate root for the CFP subdomain. It is a plain Java object — no persistence annotations, no framework dependencies. All business logic (invariants) lives here: checking submission windows, preventing duplicate proposals, enforcing track validity. A UUID is generated inside the aggregate at creation time so the object is immediately fully-formed and can be tested in isolation with plain https://junit.org/junit5/[JUnit], no container required."
msgstr "`SessionProposal` 是 CFP 子域的聚合根。它是一个普通的 Java 对象——没有持久化注解，也没有框架依赖。所有业务逻辑（不变量）都位于此处：检查提交时间窗口、防止提案重复、强制执行分会场有效性。 聚合体在创建时会内部生成一个 UUID，因此该对象立即形成完整结构，可使用纯 link:https://junit.org/junit5/[JUnit] 进行隔离测试，无需容器。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Value Objects"
msgstr "值对象"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy highlighted the `EmailAddress` value object on the `Presenter` type as a concrete example. It applies a regex pattern check at construction time and overrides `toString()` to return the address string. Validation that matters everywhere — regardless of whether input arrives via REST, https://kafka.apache.org/[Kafka], or a spreadsheet file — belongs inside the value object, not only at the API boundary."
msgstr "杰里米以 `Presenter` 类型中的 `EmailAddress` 值对象为例进行了说明。 它在构造时应用正则表达式模式检查，并重写了 `toString() 方法` 以返回地址字符串。无论输入是通过 REST、 link:https://kafka.apache.org/[Kafka] 还是电子表格文件传入的，那些在任何地方都至关重要的验证逻辑都应包含在值对象内部，而不仅仅局限于 API 边界。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The `ConferenceSessionFormat` type is another value object, this time backed by a database record (conference organizers can configure their own formats). Its identity is defined entirely by its attributes — two formats are equal if their data is equal."
msgstr "`ConferenceSessionFormat` 类型是另一个值对象，但此次由数据库记录提供支持（会议组织者可以配置自己的格式）。其身份完全由其属性定义——如果两个格式的数据相同，则它们是相等的。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Repositories and the Persistence Boundary"
msgstr "存储库与持久化边界"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The `SessionProposalRepository` wraps a https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache[Panache] repository. Critically, JPA entities never escape the `persistence` package. The repository exposes `toEntity()` and `toDomain()` marshalling methods that translate between the aggregate and the entity. Swapping the persistence backend (to https://www.mongodb.com/[MongoDB], or to a document store like https://firebase.google.com/products/firestore[Cloud Firestore] as Jeremy has done on a side project) only requires changing the repository implementation — nothing else in the application needs to change."
msgstr "`SessionProposalRepository` 封装了一个 link:https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache[Panache] 存储库。关键在于，JPA 实体永远不会脱离 `持久化` 包。 该存储库提供了 `toEntity()` 和 `toDomain()` 序列化方法，用于在聚合对象与实体之间进行转换。更换持久化后端（例如切换到 link:https://www.mongodb.com/[MongoDB] ，或者像 Jeremy 在一个副项目中所做的那样，切换到 link:https://firebase.google.com/products/firestore[Cloud Firestore] 这样的文档存储）只需修改存储库的实现即可——应用程序的其他部分无需任何更改。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Submission Context and Domain Services"
msgstr "提交上下文和域服务"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The `SubmissionContext` object deserves special attention. An aggregate should be able to make decisions without reaching into infrastructure. But sometimes it needs data from other parts of the system — in this case, whether the CFP is open, which tracks exist, and which proposals the presenter has already submitted."
msgstr "`SubmissionContext` 对象值得特别关注。聚合体应当能够在无需访问基础架构的情况下做出决策。但有时它需要系统其他部分的数据——例如，本次征稿是否开放、有哪些赛道，以及演讲者已经提交了哪些提案。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The solution is a service (sitting between the application and domain layers) that assembles this context object and hands it to the aggregate. Jeremy noted this probably belongs in the domain package as a domain service rather than the application package — a distinction worth revisiting in real projects."
msgstr "该解决方案是一个服务（位于应用程序层和领域层之间），它负责组装该上下文对象并将其传递给聚合。杰里米指出，这可能应该作为领域服务放在领域包中，而不是应用程序包中——在实际项目中，这一区分值得重新审视。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Communications Subdomain and the Outbox Pattern"
msgstr "通信子域与“发件箱”模式"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When a proposal is accepted, the system needs to notify the presenter. This is handled by a separate `communications` subdomain."
msgstr "当提案被接受时，系统需要通知提案人。此操作由一个独立的 `通信` 子域负责处理。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Why a Separate Subdomain?"
msgstr "为什么要使用独立的子域名？"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "A plain email-sending library would be a shared utility. The communications subdomain earns its place because it will own decisions about _which channel_ to use (email today, social notifications tomorrow) and _what language_ to use in the message — content decisions that belong to a distinct bounded context."
msgstr "一个简单的电子邮件发送库可以视为一个共享工具。通信子域之所以有其存在的必要，是因为它将负责决定使用 _哪种渠道_ （今天是电子邮件，明天可能是社交媒体通知）以及消息中应使用 _何种语言_ ——这些内容决策属于一个独立的边界上下文。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Integration Events vs. Domain Events"
msgstr "集成事件与领域事件"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The `SessionProposalAccepted` event is an integration event, not a domain event in the strict sense. Domain events are consumed within the same bounded context; integration events are consumed by other subdomains or services. Jeremy acknowledged the current placement in the `domain-events` package is slightly wrong — it should be in an `integration-events` package to make the distinction clear."
msgstr "`SessionProposalAccepted` 事件是一个集成事件，而非严格意义上的领域事件。 领域事件在同一边界上下文中被消费；集成事件则由其他子领域或服务消费。Jeremy 承认该事件目前放置在 `domain-events` 包中的位置略有不当——为明确区分，它应置于 `integration-events` 包中。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Outbox Pattern"
msgstr "“发件箱”模式"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Rather than firing a CDI event directly inside the `acceptProposal` transaction, Jeremy implemented the outbox pattern:"
msgstr "Jeremy 没有在 `acceptProposal` 事务内部直接触发 CDI 事件，而是实现了“出箱”模式："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When a proposal is accepted, the `SessionProposalAccepted` event is written to an `outbox` database table (with an aggregate ID, event type, timestamp, and JSON payload) inside the same transaction as the status update."
msgstr "当提案被接受时，会将 `SessionProposalAccepted` 事件写入 `“发件箱”` 数据库表中（包含聚合 ID、事件类型、时间戳和 JSON 有效载荷），该操作与状态更新处于同一事务中。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "A scheduled bean (using https://quarkus.io/guides/scheduler[Quarkus Scheduler]) polls the outbox table every 30 seconds and fires the events as CDI events."
msgstr "一个定时Bean（ link:https://quarkus.io/guides/scheduler[使用Quarkus Scheduler] ）每30秒轮询一次“outbox”表，并将事件作为CDI事件触发。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The communications subdomain catches the CDI event, writes it to its own delivery table, and a second scheduler loops through pending deliveries and sends emails via https://quarkus.io/guides/mailer[Quarkus Mailer] (visible in https://mailpit.axllent.org/[Mailpit] during development)."
msgstr "通信子域捕获 CDI 事件，将其写入自身的投递表中，然后第二个调度器会循环处理待投递的邮件，并通过 link:https://quarkus.io/guides/mailer[Quarkus Mailer] 发送电子邮件（在开发过程中可在 link:https://mailpit.axllent.org/[Mailpit] 中查看）。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "This two-phase approach means that even if the application restarts mid-flight, no events are lost. It also prevents the case where an accepted talk email is sent before the database transaction commits — a subtle but real failure mode when CDI events are fired inside a transaction."
msgstr "这种分两阶段的方法意味着，即使应用程序在运行过程中重启，也不会丢失任何事件。它还能防止在数据库事务提交之前就发送已接受的演讲确认邮件的情况——当 CDI 事件在事务内部触发时，这是一种微妙但确实存在的故障模式。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy noted the outbox code is not yet fully modelled using DDD conventions and that is intentional: you do not have to apply DDD to every corner of an application. At the boundary where the pattern genuinely helps, use it; at the plumbing layer, pragmatism is fine."
msgstr "杰里米指出，发件箱的代码尚未完全按照 DDD 规范进行建模，但这是有意为之：你不必将 DDD 应用到应用程序的每个角落。在模式真正能发挥作用的边界处，就使用它；而在基础架构层，采取务实的做法也是可以的。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Validation at Multiple Layers"
msgstr "多层验证"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "A recurring audience question: where does validation go? Jeremy's answer: at every layer that has a reason to care."
msgstr "观众经常提出的一个问题：验证该放在哪里？杰里米的回答：放在每个有理由关注它的层上。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**REST adapter** — Jakarta Validation annotations on the `SessionProposalParameters` record (not-null, not-blank, valid format)"
msgstr "*REST 适配器* — `SessionProposalParameters` 记录上的 Jakarta 验证注解（非空、非空白、格式有效）"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Value objects** — constructor-level checks (regex, range, business rules) that apply regardless of how input arrived"
msgstr "*值对象* ——无论输入如何产生，均在构造函数级别进行检查（正则表达式、范围、业务规则）"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Aggregate** — cross-field and cross-entity rules (is the CFP window open? has this presenter already submitted the maximum number of talks?)"
msgstr "*汇总* ——跨领域和跨实体的规则（CFP窗口是否开放？该演讲者是否已提交了最多场次的演讲？）"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Database** — constraints as a last line of defence"
msgstr "*数据库* ——约束作为最后一道防线"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Each layer validates for its own reasons. This is not redundancy — it is defence in depth."
msgstr "每一层都有其独特的验证依据。这并非冗余——而是深度防御。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Architecture Tests with ArchUnit"
msgstr "使用 ArchUnit 进行架构测试"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The project includes a test package that enforces architectural rules using https://www.archunit.org/[ArchUnit]. The key rules:"
msgstr "该项目包含一个测试包，该测试包使用 link:https://www.archunit.org/[ArchUnit] 来强制执行架构规则。主要规则如下："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**No cyclic dependencies** between packages"
msgstr "包之间 *不存在循环依赖*"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Subdomains communicate only through their API packages** — a class in the `communications` subdomain must not import a repository class from `cfp` directly; it must go through a published API"
msgstr "*子域仅通过其 API 包* `进行通信——通信子` 域中的类不得直接从 `cfp` 导入仓库类；必须通过已发布的 API 进行操作"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "ArchUnit tests run as part of the standard JUnit suite. For teams inheriting a \"big ball of mud\" codebase, ArchUnit's `freeze` feature is especially useful: you can freeze existing violations so that tests only fail on _new_ violations, letting you introduce DDD patterns incrementally without breaking the build from day one."
msgstr "ArchUnit 测试作为标准 JUnit 测试套件的一部分运行。对于接手了“一团乱麻”式代码库的团队而言，ArchUnit `的“冻结”` 功能尤为实用：您可以冻结现有的违规项，使测试仅 _在新出现的_ 违规项上失败，从而让您能够逐步引入 DDD 模式，而不会从第一天起就导致构建失败。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "AI Agents Following DDD Conventions"
msgstr "遵循 DDD 规范的 AI 代理"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy ran a live experiment during the episode: he gave both https://platform.openai.com/docs/assistants/overview[OpenAI Codex] and https://claude.ai/[Claude] the same specification — a minimal attendee registration subdomain — and let them generate code independently. The results were compared live."
msgstr "杰里米在本期节目中进行了一项现场实验：他向 link:https://platform.openai.com/docs/assistants/overview[OpenAI Codex] 和 link:https://claude.ai/[Claude] 提供了相同的规格说明——一个最简版的参会者注册子域名——并让它们独立生成代码。随后现场对两者的结果进行了对比。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Both agents produced structurally similar output:"
msgstr "这两个代理生成的输出在结构上相似："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Value objects for name and email"
msgstr "用于存储姓名和电子邮件的值对象"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "A command record"
msgstr "一条命令记录"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "An application service"
msgstr "一项应用服务"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "A repository"
msgstr "一个存储库"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Domain-specific exceptions"
msgstr "特定领域的异常"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Neither output was perfect (one missed Panache, neither added ArchUnit tests), but the overall structure was recognisably DDD-compliant. Jeremy's takeaway: DDD's explicit conventions about where things go — aggregates hold logic, repositories handle persistence, commands enter through the application layer — give coding agents a predictable scaffold to follow. Well-structured specifications plus DDD conventions produce more consistent generated code than under-specified CRUD codebases."
msgstr "虽然这两个输出结果都不尽完美（其中一个遗漏了 Panache，两个都没有添加 ArchUnit 测试），但整体结构显然符合 DDD 规范。 Jeremy的总结：DDD关于组件归属位置的明确约定——聚合体承载业务逻辑、存储库处理持久化、命令通过应用层进入——为编码人员提供了一个可预测的框架。结构良好的规范加上DDD约定，生成的代码比规范不足的CRUD代码库更加一致。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "He recommended spending more time writing detailed specifications and reviewing AI output than on code generation itself, and noted that adding DDD-specific skills (prompt files) to the agent configuration improves adherence to patterns like correct placement of business logic, value object validation, and ArchUnit rule compliance."
msgstr "他建议将更多时间用于编写详细的规格说明和审查 AI 生成的结果，而不是花在代码生成本身上；他还指出，在代理配置中添加 DDD 特定技能（提示文件），有助于更好地遵循相关模式，例如业务逻辑的正确放置、值对象的验证以及 ArchUnit 规则的遵守。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Upcoming"
msgstr "即将推出"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Jeremy mentioned he is preparing an updated hands-on workshop (cloneable from GitHub) based on this material, and will be co-presenting a similar workshop with Rob Cedor at https://exploreddd.com/[Explore DDD] in Colorado in September. The next Quarkus Insights (skipping two weeks for the summer schedule) will cover Quarkus in the real world — an experience report with real-world performance metrics."
msgstr "杰里米提到，他正在根据这些材料准备一个更新版的动手实践工作坊（可从 GitHub 克隆），并将于 9 月在科罗拉多州举办的 link:https://exploreddd.com/[Explore DDD] 大会上与 Rob Cedor 共同主持一个类似的工作坊。 下一期《Quarkus Insights》（因夏季日程安排将暂停两周）将探讨 Quarkus 在实际应用中的表现——这是一份包含实际性能指标的经验报告。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Key Takeaways"
msgstr "要点总结"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Commands are the API between adapters and the application core** — any adapter (REST, messaging, file) creates the same command and passes it to the same service."
msgstr "*命令是适配器与应用程序核心之间的 API* ——任何适配器（REST、消息传递、文件）都会生成相同的命令，并将其传递给同一个服务。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Aggregates own all business logic** — invariants, UUID generation, event creation. They are plain Java objects, testable without a container."
msgstr "*聚合类包含所有业务逻辑* ——不变量、UUID 生成、事件创建。它们是普通的 Java 对象，无需容器即可进行测试。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**The persistence boundary is absolute** — JPA entities live only inside the repository; nothing outside the `persistence` package imports them."
msgstr "*持久化边界是绝对的* ——JPA 实体仅存在于存储库内部； `持久化` 包之外没有任何内容会导入它们。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**The Submission Context pattern** lets aggregates make informed decisions without knowing about infrastructure."
msgstr "*“提交上下文”模式* 使聚合体能够在无需了解基础设施的情况下做出明智的决策。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**The outbox pattern** decouples event publishing from the originating transaction, preventing lost events and premature notifications."
msgstr "*“发件箱”模式将* 事件发布与源事务解耦，从而防止事件丢失和过早通知。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Integration events and domain events are different** — name and package them accordingly."
msgstr "*集成事件和领域事件是不同的* ——请根据其性质分别命名并将其归入相应的包中。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**Validation belongs at every layer** for different reasons; value objects enforce rules that apply regardless of input source."
msgstr "出于不同的原因， *验证应贯穿每个层* ；值对象会强制执行无论输入来源如何都适用的规则。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**ArchUnit enforces subdomain boundaries** as part of the test suite, with a freeze option for incremental adoption in legacy codebases."
msgstr "*ArchUnit* 作为测试套件的一部分 *，强制执行子域边界* ，并提供“冻结”选项，以便在旧版代码库中逐步采用。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**DDD conventions make AI-generated code more predictable** — structured specifications plus explicit patterns produce consistent output across different agents."
msgstr "*DDD 规范使 AI 生成的代码更具可预测性* ——结构化的规范加上明确的模式，可在不同代理之间产生一致的输出。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "**You don't have to apply DDD everywhere** — be pragmatic at the plumbing layer; reserve the extra ceremony for areas where the business logic complexity justifies it."
msgstr "*不必在所有地方都应用领域驱动设计（DDD）* ——在基础架构层要务实；将额外的繁文缛节留给那些因业务逻辑复杂性而确实需要的地方。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr "结论"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-07-14-quarkus-insights-254-ddd-hexagonal-architecture-part2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Episode 254 makes the DDD discussion concrete with a complete, runnable application. The call-for-papers demo shows how patterns introduced in episode 248 — aggregates, value objects, commands, and domain events — play out across a full request lifecycle, including cross-subdomain collaboration via the outbox pattern and enforceable architecture rules. The live AI coding experiment adds a timely angle: as development teams lean more heavily on coding agents, the predictable structure of DDD may be one of its strongest arguments in a world where generated code needs to be reviewable and maintainable."
msgstr "第 254 集通过一个完整且可运行的应用程序，将 DDD 的讨论具体化。 在“征稿”演示中，展示了第248期介绍的模式——聚合、值对象、命令和领域事件——如何贯穿整个请求生命周期，包括通过“发件箱”模式实现的跨子域协作以及可强制执行的架构规则。 现场人工智能编码实验则提供了极具现实意义的视角：随着开发团队越来越依赖编码代理，在生成代码必须可审查且可维护的当今世界，DDD 可预测的结构或许正是其最具说服力的优势之一。"

